.TH "ssam_controller_lock" 9 "ssam_controller_lock" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ssam_controller_lock \- Acquire the main controller lock.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ssam_controller_lock
.BI "(struct ssam_controller *c "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
The controller to lock.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This lock must be held for any state transitions, including transition to
suspend/resumed states and during shutdown. See \fBssam_controller_statelock\fP
for more details on controller locking.

See \fBssam_controller_unlock\fP for the corresponding unlock function.
